EXCEL COLUMN SPECS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Creator Excel (8 columns; case-INSENSITIVE header match):
    Employee ID -> resource_id (int)
    Project ID -> project_id (int)
    Product ID -> product_id (int)
    Task Index -> task_idx (int)
    Activity Index -> activity_idx (int)
    Start Date -> start_date (YYYY-MM-DD string)
    End Date -> end_date (YYYY-MM-DD string)
    Planned Hours -> plan_hrs (float)

Reviewer Excel (4 columns):
    Task ID -> worklog_idx (int)  # the task's WorkLogIdx
    Date -> task_date (YYYY-MM-DD)
    Hours -> hours (float)
    Remark -> remarks (string)
    NOTE: Resource is always the logged-in user. Ignore any
    "Employee ID" column in the file.

Approver Excel (1 column):
    Worklog ID -> worklog_log_idx (int)  # the Idx in pp_worklogs_demo
    Action is always APPROVE. Rejection not supported via Excel.

For all three, the upload pipeline already places parsed file content
in state["uploaded_files"] as a list of dicts with shape:
    {"filename": "...", "file_type": "excel", "row_count": N,
     "data": [ {col: val, col: val, ...}, ... ], "preview": [...]}
We use the "data" list. Each item is one row as a dict keyed by
column header.

