HELPER: column-name resolver (case-insensitive header lookup)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Add helper near the existing extraction helpers:

def _get_cell(row: dict, *candidates) -> any:
    """Case-insensitive cell lookup. Returns the first non-None
    value among candidate header names; otherwise None."""
    if not row:
        return None
    lower_map = {str(k).strip().lower(): v for k, v in row.items()}
    for cand in candidates:
        val = lower_map.get(cand.strip().lower())
        if val is not None and str(val).strip() != "":
            return val
    return None

This handles "Employee ID" / "employee id" / "Employee Id" all the
same way, and treats blank cells as missing.

